id: pm-orrl
title: "pm create --blocked-by stores free-text metadata, not a dependency edge or blocked status (agent-confusing)"
description: "Dogfood (2026-05-20): pm create --type Task --blocked-by pm-xxxx sets blocked_by:'pm-xxxx' as metadata but creates no dependency edge (pm deps shows edge_count 0) and leaves status=open (not blocked). Help text says '--blocked-by <value> Blocked-by item ID or reason', so it is intentionally free-text, distinct from --dep which creates real edges. Agents reasonably expect blocked-by to create an edge and/or set blocked status. Decision needed: (a) when the value resolves to a valid item id, also create a blocks/blocked-by dependency edge (and optionally set status=blocked), or (b) sharpen help/docs to make the metadata-vs-edge distinction explicit and point to --dep for edges. Recommend (a) for the id case with (b) wording as a fallback."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-ux,cli,create,dependencies,dogfood
created_at: "2026-05-20T20:32:50.496Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-21T17:41:37.203Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: "Behavior of --blocked-by is unambiguous: either it creates a real dependency edge (and documents status implications) when given a valid item id, or help/docs clearly state it is free-text metadata distinct from --dep; chosen behavior is tested."
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: "pm create --blocked-by now derives a real blocked_by dependency edge when the value resolves to an existing item id, defaults status to blocked only when status is omitted, preserves explicit statuses, and keeps free-text reasons as metadata only."
expected_result: Agents can use --blocked-by with an item id and get dependency graph semantics without losing the free-text reason workflow.
actual_result: "Focused tests and manual temp-project smoke verified dependency edge_count=1 with via=blocked_by, free-text fallback, explicit-status preservation, and dedupe behavior."
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-21T17:27:14.467Z",codex-gpt5,"Execution start 2026-05-21: duplicate check reused existing pm-orrl under pm-rnpb. Sub-agent review found pm plan already maps blocked-by to kind=blocked_by dependencies; implementing create behavior to derive a real edge only when the blocked-by value resolves to an existing pm item, preserving free-text metadata fallback."
  "2026-05-21T17:40:17.167Z",codex-gpt5,"Evidence 2026-05-21: implemented create --blocked-by semantics for existing item IDs. The CLI preserves blocked_by metadata, derives one blocked_by dependency edge when the value resolves to an existing item, defaults status to blocked only when status was omitted, preserves explicit statuses, and keeps free-text reasons as metadata without edges. Manual temp-project smoke verified deps edge_count=1 and via=blocked_by. Verification passed: focused blocked-by suite, combined focused suite 8 files / 310 tests, package-first dogfood 84 workflows, semantic dogfood 86 workflows, and full release gate 96 files / 1406 tests at 100 percent coverage plus required Sentry/telemetry."
